            "answer_text": "Louis XIII suffered from pre-mature balding. The popular style at the time was long curly hair. It was known in England as the Cavalier style. He popularized wearing wigs. His successor Louis XIV mandated that all men wear a hat, wig, cravat, shirt, vest, long coat, side sword, knee breeches, silk socks and shoes to court. ",
